npm init
• Makes the package.json project management document


npm install --save express
• Install express packages
• --save tag updates the package.json


create book.js
- require express
- start server
- print console message
• Set up the main file to start the server
• Ensure the server can handle errors


Update package.json with book.js (or main file name)
• Ensures that the files are tied together


Templating Setup
- npm install --save express3-handlebars
- edit book.js with handlebars require statement
• Reduces the amount of repetitive code to write
• Makes maintenance easier


Create Default Template + Views
- create views/layouts directories
- create main.handlebars view (default view)
- create individual page views (these go into the main view)
- add error handling views

Begin adding routes for pages
• Route pages as appropriate
• Add page error handling + views


Database
- navigate to MongoDB folder (c:\Program Files\MongoDB\Server\3.2\bin)
- run MongoDB project install (mongod --dbpath c:\...) (to the data folder in the actual project)
- open a second terminal and type mongo in the MongoDB folder (.../bin)
- create database (> use bookdb)
- add in MongoDB, Monk, and database requirements
- add in route for db above all other routes
- add test entry for collection (insert.usercollection...)
- apply functions for adding/reading database


